Frontier Airlines to charge for hand luggage
Frontier Airlines plans to charge up to $100 for hand luggage on board during its flights.
Frontier Airlines plans to introduce a fee of up to $100 for hand luggage and $2 for coffee or soda, though in their announcement on Wednesday they said passengers would be able to keep the entire can.
The new carry-on baggage charge applies to luggage in the upper storage compartment, so small bags under the seat will continue to be free.
